    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MIB length validation in broadcast detect indication packing\n\n### Summary\nThe broadcast detect indication packing functions in the nFAPI library were missing validation of the MIB length parameter before attempting to pack the MIB data array. This could lead to buffer overruns when packing messages with invalid MIB lengths.\n\nThis fix adds proper validation to the LTE, UTRAN, and NB-IOT broadcast detect indication packing functions to check that mib_length does not exceed NFAPI_MAX_MIB_LENGTH before calling pusharray8.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p4.c`: Added MIB length validation in pack_lte_broadcast_detect_indication_value, pack_utran_broadcast_detect_indication_value, and pack_nb_iot_broadcast_detect_indication_value functions.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Create a nfapi_lte_broadcast_detect_indication_t structure\n2. Set mib_length to a value greater than NFAPI_MAX_MIB_LENGTH (32)\n3. Call pack_lte_broadcast_detect_indication_value() \n4. Observe that the function fails silently without clear error reporting\n\nAfter the fix, the same scenario will properly log an error message \"MIB too long\" and return 0, matching the behavior of the corresponding unpack functions.\n"
}